OL,3,CCare home apologises to families over
OL,4,Cstring of failures
OL,6,FA Gloucestershire care provider has
OL,7,Fapologised and changed its management
OL,8,Fafter complaints over poor record
OL,9,Fkeeping, cleaning, food provision and
OL,10,Fdata breaches against them were upheld.
OL,12,FTwo separate complaints lodged with
OL,13,Fthe Local Governent and Social Care
OL,14,FOmbudsman against Lilian Faithfull
OL,15,FCare were upheld on 27 June.
OL,17,FThe first of the complaints referred
OL,18,Fto the standard of care a woman's late
OL,19,Fmother received while a resident at
OL,20,FAstell House Care Home in Cheltenham.
