OL,3,CCare home apologises to families over
OL,4,Cstring of failures
OL,6,FIt was also claimed that the care home
OL,7,Fdid not carry out an initial three-
OL,8,Fmonth care review with the family as
OL,9,Fpromised in the care home
OL,10,Fdocumentation. Additionally, the woman
OL,11,Fsaid that record keeping at Astell
OL,12,FHouse was poor and her mother suffered
OL,13,Ffrom poor pain management.
OL,15,FIn the complaint, the woman said that
OL,16,Fshe and her family had experienced
OL,17,Fsever distress and frustration due to
OL,18,Fthe care her mother received at the
OL,19,Fhome, but Lilian Faithfull Care had
OL,20,Fnot provided an adequate response.
