OL,3,CCare home apologises to families over
OL,4,Cstring of failures
OL,6,FThe care provider agreed to apologise
OL,7,Fto the women in question, saying that
OL,8,Flessons had been learned and actions
OL,9,Fwould be taken to address the issues
OL,10,Fshe brought forward.
OL,12,FThe care home also agreed to review
OL,13,Fthe accuracy of its overall record
OL,14,Fkeeping and consider how to streamline
OL,15,Fthe process within 12 weeks. Lilian
OL,16,FFaithfull Care will also have to
OL,17,Fsupply the ombudsman with evidence of
OL,18,Ftheir new processes.
